{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a \u201cdirect democracy\u201d framework",
        "additional_details": "Introducing a more direct democracy based on Switzerland\u2019s framework \u2013 where many decisions are automatically put to a referendum and citizens can propose constitutional changes or ask for referendums on other matters \u2013 would give the power to the people instead of the government.\r\n \r\nWe believe recent events, including the Government\u2019s response to the Covid-19 outbreak, has demonstrated that the people should be given a choice and a say on what is best for us.",
        "background": "Introduce a \u201cdirect democracy\u201d framework that enables all UK citizens over the age of 18 to vote and decision-make on how our country is run, based on Switzerland\u2019s framework. The fundamental principle of direct democracy is that all citizens take part in all decision-making.",
